WHAT'S CHANGEDChagee Holdings Ltd (CHA.O)FromToPrice TargetUS$32.50US$28.00Bull CaseUS$38.50US$33.00Base CaseUS$32.50US$28.00Bear CaseUS$17.50US$15.00Updated ComponentsEPSBull Base Bear Scenarios

We trim our 2025 earnings estimate by \(14\%\) , factoring in 2Q25 results and sustained pressure from delivery platform subsidies on both ASP and order counts for Chagee. We also expect some operating deleveraging impact on the company on the declining unit GMV, as it continues to opt out from participating from the platform's subsidies program. As such, we lower our 2025 sales forecast by \(6\%\) , projecting fully- year avg. China monthly unit GMV at \(\sim \mathsf{Rmb}380\mathrm{k}\) (vs \(\sim \mathsf{Rmb}390\mathrm{k}\) previously, implying nearly \(\mathsf{Rmb}360\mathrm{k}\) average monthly unit GMV in 2H25), with 900 new openings in China (vs. previous 1,000). Given the lower base in 2025, we cut our 2026/2027 earnings by \(14\%\) .
Our PT is now US \(28, vs\) 32.5 previously, as a result of the earnings change. Our bull/bear case values are lowered accordingly.
While the subsidy situation remains fluid, timing of subsidies retreating on delivery platforms and impact to unit GMV are key to watch in the near term.

Revolutionizing the Tea-drinking Experience
Chagee is a well- established brand in the freshly brewed tea industry, and the leader in the premium segment by store count and GMV.
It is in a brand- power- growing stage. We expect GMV growth to outperform industry peers, given a better payback period and store operating margin.

We think its replicable business model can be adopted overseas and provide upside. The stock trades at 12x our 2025e P/E, a discount to its peers, which we find attractive, factoring in Chagee's leading market position in the premium category with global expansion opportunities.

Per- store GMV grows, driven by new product launches and stronger- than- expected recovery in traffic; pace of store opening is ahead of company target: We assume (1) overall per- store GMV at Rmb388k/month (SSSG down 21.5% yoy), with store growth at 4% YoY in 2025e; and (2) 12% revenue app 4% net profit CAGRs, 2024- 26e.

Per- store GMV starts to stabilize in 2026, and pace of store openings is largely in- line with company target: We expect (1) overall per- store GMV of Rmb378k/month (SSSG down 23.5% yoy), with average store growth at 41% YoY in 2025e; and (2) 9% revenue and 1% net profit CAGRs, 2024- 26e.

Per- store GMV deteriorates despite slowdown in pace of store openings: We assume (1) overall per- store GMV drops to Rmb368k/month (SSSG down 25.5% yoy), and pace of store expansion slows to an average of 40% YoY in 2025e; and (2) 1.3% revenue CAGR in 2024- 26e while Net Profit declining at 7.2% CAGR during the same period.
